This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with object tracking, which is a common task in computer vision. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning, which is a popular technique in computer vision research and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the paper proposes an adaptive fusion approach, which involves making decisions based on the data, and this falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also discusses the challenges of tracking, which involves dealing with noisy and uncertain data, and this falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on four challenging datasets, which involves analyzing and processing large amounts of data, and this falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
